args: This is it. Today, I tell her my true feelings!
Please hold that thought a moment.\nI hope this box in front of the door\nisn't what I fear it is.
...I knew it! It's full of fiend fur!\nThis is clearly your doing, Rodrigo.
It certainly is! How does it find you?
Do you not sense the difference between\nit and the previous pelts I've given you?\nIt is so soft! So luxurious! So delightful!

It came from a fiend, Rodrigo—there's
nothing delightful about it. Now please
take this away and stop trying to make
my life difficult.
Oh dear. It seems I have failed again.
Er, it's Jakob, yes? Might I inquire as to\nwhy you are staring at me?
Why are you making Cleo's life difficult?
Tell me at once! And if I don't like your\nanswer, I will... I will...
I am not TRYING to make her life difficult,\nsir! I am trying to make it happy!
Well, I mean, I SUPPOSE there may\nbe another aim in all of this, but...
Bah! I don't have to answer to you!\nWhy are you so desperate to defend\nthe woman anyway?
I just...want her to be safe.
Hmm? Methinks I smell a rat hiding\nin that non-answer of yours.
Wait, don't tell me you're also in—
What, me? No! Wait. Yes. Yes? No. Wait.
The two men glared as sparks flew in the air\nbetween them. And then...
Cleo, my dear! I bring a new present\nthat will fill your heart with wonder!
I am growing increasingly weary of\nhaving this conversation with you.
This is not a pelt, I promise! Instead,\nI've brought a pair of bloody fiend talon—
I DON'T WANT ANY FIEND BITS,\nYOU DAFT MAN!
Stop following me hither and yon like\nsome kind of cowardly shadow! If you\nhave something to ask me, then do it!
Honestly, the two of you are even stranger\nthan normal today. Did something happen?
I suppose one might say that, yes.
You know what? I don't think I really care.\nNow both of you go cool your heads\nsomewhere until you're more...normal!
She's right. We ARE acting strangely.
Instead of making her happy, we're having\nthe opposite effect—AND getting shouted\nat in the process!
Perhaps we should declare a truce,\nyou and I.
I was hoping this might turn into more\nof a give-and-take type of conversation.
Aaaah. So THAT'S why you are unable\nto confess your true feelings to her.\nAn unenviable position indeed.
And you can't seem to give her a present\nthat doesn't make her flee in terror.
Just so. Apparently I lack any concept\nof what to give a person besides random\nbits from a monster.
I was raised by a band of rough-and-\ntumble mercenaries, so the world of\ngift-giving is all a little beyond me.
Truly? Ha ha! What a funny coincidence!\nIt is little wonder we're both having so\nmuch trouble here.
Let me ask your opinion on something.\nOh, and a simple ＂yes＂ or ＂no＂ is fine.
No need to thank me! Now then, I don't\nthink the way we're currently going about\nthings is going to get us anywhere.
So what say we put our heads together\nand try and think of a way to tell Cleo\nhow we feel TOGETHER?
I can promise nothing—but seeing as how\nwe come from similar backgrounds, I have\na suspicion we might work well together.

The only other option is to go ask someone
who knows more about this kind of thing—
but I'm honestly not certain I'd even
understand such advice.
You see? Now let us put our heads\ntogether and see what we can figure out!

After much thought, the pair decided to craft
a present for Cleo together. For since mercenaries 
maintain their own gear, they were both quite
skilled with their hands.
And so, a few days later...
There she is. Let us see this thing done!
Did it come from a fiend? Did it even\nTOUCH a fiend? If so, I don't want it.
It's...not from a fiend. It's... Um...
Enough, Jakob. I shall speak\nfor the both of us.
This is no fiend, Cleo—it is a small bear\nstatue carved from wood.
And you're certain it's not actually from\nsome tree-fiend that you chopped down?\n...Very well. I suppose I can accept it.
Goodness, this is quite skillfully done.\nThank you, Rodrigo.
Actually, this was made by me and...
(Hold a moment. Jakob is barely able\nto sputter out two words in front of Cleo.)
(That means I could pass this off as\na creation entirely my own!)
J-just that this present comes from\nboth Jakob and myself.
We poured our hearts into making it,\nto tell you how we feel about you.\nFor you see, I... No, WE... Um...
And it just makes me all the more happy.\nTo be honest, I've never been given a\npresent like this before.
I am so glad you understand!
I certainly do—this is your apology for\ngetting in the way of my work of late!
I now fully understand how sorry you are.\nNow, if you'll excuse me?
Still, we DID make her happy.\nThat's better than nothing.
Well then, no sense in breaking up a\ngood thing. Let's continue striving to\nmake her happy together!
